 from uznerk mcl ucsb edu andrew krenz subject re impala ss going into production distribution na lines four zero in dunnjj ucsu colorado edu dunn jonathan james writes uznerk mcl ucsb edu andrew krenz writes i personally like the looks of the impala ss the caprice was definately weird looking until this year when they made the rear wheel openings look more like a normal car but the impala impresses me gm can t exactly shove the lt one in everything they make you know only the bigger stuff i d like to see it next in a one five zero zero series pickup that would be a hot setup what about in a full size blazer as well would this engine have the gobs of torque necessary for off roading if so this would be even better than the syclone well an lt one blazer wouldn t come close to a gmc typhoon in speed i think its too heavy as it is right now the normal two one zero hp five seven engine has plenty of power for a full size blazer of course i m not saying gm shouldn t put the lt one in it it seems like they have a real winner with that engine why spend so much more money into getting a three two valve dohc v eight when you can take an lt one it even seems to get pretty good gas mpg for a five seven that is talking about impala ss will this be in the four door caprice body i m just curious if chevy is trying to resurrect their two door muscle cars or to compete with the european super sedans yeah it s a flat black lowered four door caprice riding on one seven aluminum rims and eagle gs c tires the rest of the car is basically a caprice ltz read plush police package with three zero zero horsepower i heard that chevy is resurrecting the monte carlo but that s going to get their three four dohc v six and not the lt one jon dunn andrew krenz uznerk mcl ucsb edu krenz engrhub ucsb edu